{
  "text": "-9 - [CITATION_1] . Local superfusion of SKA-31 over the cremaster muscle induced a concentration-dependent dilation in wt arterioles that was significantly larger than the subtle diameter changes triggered by superfusing the solvent (cremophor) alone ( dilations that were significantly stronger than dilations induced by ACh alone suggesting an additive effect of these dilators except for the highest concentrations of ACh used (Fig.S1 ).",
